commit.message: Declare bv2nat and nat2bv instead of bv2int and int2bv
Return null if there is a type error
CC fixes
Fix typo in 8aa87cd61f006b1612297f7d2848141cfb80ec97

Do type checking of parameters

Co-authored-by: Jochen Hoenicke <hoenicke@gmail.com>

Add support for bv2int and for int2bv

* Both functions are not (yet?) in the SMT-LIB standard.
* Z3 supports both functions.
* We want to utilize this functions internally for our translation from
  bitvectors to integers.
* As an alternative, people also discuss the functions bv2nat and
  nat2bv. https://groups.google.com/g/smt-lib/c/-GJG1Pq61hI
  However, I strongly prefer a totally defined function over a partially
  defined function.
updated proof document
Added trailing newlines
Some more clean-ups, test for mixed cycles
simplified open/close path into one function
Simplified index handling
Refactored cycle interpolator into a new class
Reviewed all except Cycle-Conflict
Removed dead branches and add assert that it's dead.

fix bug in incremental DataTypeTheory

Make recheckOnBacktrack scoped so it removes terms that are popped from
context.  Also remove all lemmas and recheck after pop.
Fix interpolation of dt_constructor lemma

Better error handling/reporting.

Fix exception when datatype is declared twice
Fix datatype interpolation tests
uploaded tests for datatype interpolation
fixed error in dt_cycle, inserted parts for dt_cases and dt_tester
fixed interpolation for datatype cycles
updated datatype interpolator
added interpolation for datatypes

Improved error handling for getFunction()

Instead of returning null getFunction() and getFunctionWithResult()
now return an exception if the function does not exits.  Improved the
error message for this case.

There were only a few caller that checked for null, remove the check there.
Also had to rework the IRA hack slightly.

Don't unshare ccterm when deconstructing

Instead of unsharing CCTerms when they are removed on pop, they are only
unshared by the clausifier, explicitly.  If the term is removed the shared term
will not be used anyways.
There was a bug before where pop() happens in different order and the same
term was unshared twice.

Fixes #145

Remove FunFactory scopes in resetAssertions.

This fixes #144
started new slides
fix unit tests
add option for reproducible-resource-limit (#140)
